What's the status on this?
There really needs to be a way to access the transaction that will be used for the `save` in any of the hooks.
That way you could do something like
```
Parent.beforeUpdate( async (parent, options, transaction) => {
if (options.include && options.include.indexOf(Child) > -1 && parent.child) {
return await parent.child.save({ transaction })
}
});
```
This way associations can automatically updated and rolled back, rather than having to manually manage the transactions every time you need to update associations.
This gets especially painful when handling multiple top level associations or deep nested associations.
